READ -> METHOD = {GET} URL = https://thememeri-api-v1.herokuapp.com/Api

CREATE -> METHOD = {POST} URL = https://thememeri-api-v1.herokuapp.com/Api/create/{EmployeeName}

UPDATE -> METHOD = {POST} URL = https://thememeri-api-v1.herokuapp.com/Api/update/{EmployeeID}/{NewEmployName}

DELETE -> METHOD = {DELETE} URL = https://thememeri-api-v1.herokuapp.com/Api/delete/{EmployeeID}

JWT Auth -> METHOD = {GET} URL = https://thememeri-api-v1.herokuapp.com/Api/AuthorizedPage you can acces this either by JWT token or session login

Login -> {POST} URL = https://thememeri-api-v1.herokuapp.com/Api/login/{EmployeeId}/{EmployeeName

in order to get JWT token and get authorized to the AuthorizedPage you need to login first :

By loging in you will get JWT token, if you are using POSTMAN send a GET request https://ancient-springs-32831.herokuapp.com/Api/AuthorizedPage with Header key Authorization and value <Bearer {JWT_Token}>
